==Awards and nominations==
{{Main|List of awards and nominations received by Morgan Freeman}}
Freeman has been recognized by the [[Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences]] for the following performances:
*[[60th Academy Awards]]: Best Supporting Actor, nomination, for ''Street Smart'' (1987)<ref name=":10" />
*[[62nd Academy Awards]]: Best Actor, nomination, for ''Driving Miss Daisy'' (1989)<ref name=":1" />
*[[67th Academy Awards]]: Best Actor, nomination, for ''The Shawshank Redemption'' (1994)<ref name=":11" />
*[[77th Academy Awards]]: Best Supporting Actor, '''win''', for ''Million Dollar Baby'' (2004)<ref>{{Cite web|title=The 77th Academy Awards {{!}} 2005|url=https://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/2005|access-date=2021-03-20|website=Oscars.org {{!}} Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences|language=en|archive-date=January 1, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160101230853/http://oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/2005|url-status=live}}</ref>
*[[82nd Academy Awards]]: Best Actor, nomination, for ''Invictus'' (2009)<ref>{{Cite web|title=The 82nd Academy Awards {{!}} 2010|url=https://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/2010|access-date=2021-03-20|website=Oscars.org {{!}} Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences|language=en|archive-date=April 17, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180417095231/https://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/2010|url-status=live}}</ref>

Freeman has been nominated for five Golden Globe Awards, winning one for [[Golden Globe Award for Best Actor - Motion Picture Musical or Comedy|Best Actor]] in ''Driving Miss Daisy'' (1989).<ref>{{Cite web|title=Morgan Freeman|url=https://www.goldenglobes.com/person/morgan-freeman|access-date=2020-08-01|website=www.goldenglobes.com|language=en|archive-date=March 20, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210320142902/https://www.goldenglobes.com/person/morgan-freeman|url-status=live}}</ref> He has also been nominated for three [[Screen Actors Guild Awards]], winning one for [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Male Actor in a Supporting Role|Outstanding Performance by a Male Actor in a Supporting Role]] in ''Million Dollar Baby'' (2004)''.''<ref>{{Cite web|title=The 11th Annual Screen Actors Guild Awards {{!}} Screen Actors Guild Awards|url=http://www.sagawards.org/awards/nominees-and-recipients/11th-annual-screen-actors-guild-awards|access-date=2020-08-01|website=www.sagawards.org|language=en|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6IEnZ4GcL?url=http://www.sagawards.org/awards/nominees-and-recipients/11th-annual-screen-actors-guild-awards|archive-date=July 19, 2013|url-status=live}}</ref> He earned an [[Obie Award]] for each theatre role in ''Coriolanus'' (1979)'', [[Mother Courage and Her Children]]'' (1980)'','' and ''Driving Miss Daisy'' (1987–90)''.''<ref name=":7" />

